# Authentication Features for Keepr

Build complete authentication (Login, Register, Google Login, Organization, Profile, Logout) in the existing Keepr Next.js 16 app, with a focus on **learning** each concept: Middleware, Cookies, Protected Routes, Headers, and Server Components.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database choice**: This plan uses **Prisma + PostgreSQL** for data storage. If you prefer a different database (MySQL, SQLite for local dev, MongoDB), let me know.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Google OAuth**: You will need to create a Google Cloud project and obtain `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` from the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials). We'll set up the redirect URI as `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google/callback`.

> [!WARNING]
> **No NextAuth/Auth.js**: To maximize learning, we are building auth **from scratch** — manually handling JWTs, cookies, middleware, and OAuth. This is intentional so you understand what libraries like NextAuth abstract away.

