## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Browser"
        A["Login/Register Pages<br/>(Client Components)"]
    end

    subgraph "Next.js Server"
        B["API Routes<br/>/api/auth/*"]
        C["Middleware<br/>middleware.ts"]
        D["Protected Pages<br/>(Server Components)"]
        E["Cookies<br/>(HttpOnly JWT)"]
    end

    subgraph "Database"
        F["PostgreSQL<br/>via Prisma"]
    end

    A -->|"POST form data"| B
    B -->|"Set cookie"| E
    B -->|"Read/Write"| F
    C -->|"Check cookie on every request"| E
    C -->|"Allow or redirect"| D
    D -->|"Read user from cookie"| E
    D -->|"Fetch user data"| F
```

### Key Concepts You'll Learn

| Concept | Where You'll See It | What It Does |
|---------|-------------------|--------------|
| **Middleware** | `middleware.ts` | Runs BEFORE every request — checks if user is logged in |
| **Cookies** | `lib/auth.ts` | Stores JWT token securely in the browser (HttpOnly) |
| **Protected Routes** | `middleware.ts` + layouts | Redirects unauthenticated users to `/login` |
| **Headers** | API routes + middleware | Reads/sets HTTP headers (Authorization, Set-Cookie) |
| **Server Components** | Profile page, workspace layout | Fetches data on the server — never exposes secrets to the browser |

