### 3. Auth Library (Core Logic)

#### [NEW] [auth.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/lib/auth.ts)

The heart of the auth system. Contains:

- `hashPassword(password)` — hash a password with bcrypt
- `verifyPassword(password, hash)` — compare password to hash
- `createToken(userId)` — create a JWT signed with a secret
- `verifyToken(token)` — verify and decode the JWT
- `setAuthCookie(token)` — set the JWT as an HttpOnly cookie
- `removeAuthCookie()` — delete the cookie (logout)
- `getAuthFromCookies()` — read the JWT from cookies, return the user ID

**🍪 Cookies Learning Point**: We use `HttpOnly` cookies so JavaScript in the browser **cannot** read the token — this prevents XSS attacks. The cookie is sent automatically with every request.

#### [NEW] [db.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/lib/db.ts)

Singleton Prisma client (standard Next.js pattern to avoid creating too many database connections in dev).

