### 5. API Routes

All API routes live under `/api/auth/`. They handle form submissions and return JSON.

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/app/api/auth/register/route.ts)
**POST /api/auth/register** — Creates a new user:
1. Validate name, email, password
2. Check if email already exists
3. Hash the password
4. Create user in database
5. Create a JWT token
6. Set the token as a cookie
7. Return success + redirect URL

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/app/api/auth/login/route.ts)
**POST /api/auth/login** — Logs in an existing user:
1. Find user by email
2. Compare password with hash
3. Create JWT → set cookie → return success

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/app/api/auth/logout/route.ts)
**POST /api/auth/logout** — Clears the auth cookie.

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/app/api/auth/me/route.ts)
**GET /api/auth/me** — Returns the current user's profile (used by client components).

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/app/api/auth/google/route.ts)
**GET /api/auth/google** — Redirects user to Google's OAuth consent page.

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/dl/Desktop/Main_Projects_V2/100xproject/3-slate/app/api/auth/google/callback/route.ts)
**GET /api/auth/google/callback** — Google calls this with an auth code. We:
1. Exchange code for tokens
2. Get user info from Google
3. Find or create user in our database
4. Set auth cookie → redirect to `/workspace`

